A pastor, a state trooper and a convicted sex offender were among those apprehended. CAPE TOWN - Nearly 1,000 people linked to sex trafficking have been arrested in the United States. A pastor, a state trooper and a convicted sex offender were among those apprehended. The arrests were part of the National Johns Suppression Initiative, a series of stings aimed at reducing sex trafficking across the country. Authorities cracked down on three Illinois brothels and arrested a convicted child molester in Seattle.About 170 people have been arrested in Harris County, Texas.